The paper discusses the statistical analysis of citation impact, which is a topic relevant to several sub-categories in computer science. However, given the focus on bibliometrics and publication analysis, the most likely sub-category is cs.DL (Digital Libraries). Other relevant sub-categories include cs.IR (Information Retrieval), cs.CY (Computational Geometry), cs.SI (Social and Information Networks), and cs.CR (Cryptography and Security).
